51.6	Daniel_Bernoulli	Daniel Bernoulli	Daniel Bernoulli (Groningen, 29 January 1700 â€“ Basel, 17 March 1782) was a Swiss mathematician and was one of the many prominent mathematicians in the Bernoulli family. He is particularly remembered for his applications of mathematics to mechanics, especially fluid mechanics, and for his pioneering work in probability and statistics. Bernoulli's work is still studied at length by many schools of science throughout the world.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Daniel_Bernoulli_001.jpg/260px-Daniel_Bernoulli_001.jpg
